<p>Put the commanded voltage and <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> error onto the dashboard when running this routine. Your kV seems really low.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":36,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T11:39:15.262Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":163,"readers_count":162,"score":52.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495759,"topic_slug":"time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so/495759/2","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558216,"name":"Benji Brunner","username":"Blengis","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/blengis/{size}/223194_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T13:14:40.523Z","cooked":"<p>Any possibility it’s a mechanical issue (e.g. too much friction in the elevator)? We had a similar issue, though we use a <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> and have different rigging than a GrayT. Greasing all pulleys, axles, etc might help if you’re desperate</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":36,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T13:14:40.523Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":157,"readers_count":156,"score":36.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":495759,"topic_slug":"time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so","display_username":"Benji Brunner","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65795,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2823 Alum"},"post_url":"/t/time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so/495759/3","custom_user_title":"2823 Alum","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558254,"name":"Jeffrey Davis","username":"Practicality","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/practicality/{size}/208492_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T13:45:59.780Z","cooked":"<p>These might seem like dumb questions but mignt help:</p>
<p>Are you holding in the A button during your test? The code you have cancels as soon as A is released so you have to keep holding it in.</p>
<p>Where did the P value come from? It seems very precise but if its not enough to move the elevator it might just be too low of a value ( or your other constants are too low)</p>
<p>Are there any other commands that could be running and cancelling this command? Something checking a sensor or a limit switch that is running any other command on the subsystem? (Remember a subsystem can only run one command at a time so any other commands will cancel this one).</p>
<p>Have your been able to move the elevator with simpler command? Set a voltage in the right direction and see if it moves? (Be ready on e stop for that one of course). Work your way up in steps like .1% power, 1% power, 5%, 10% and see if you start getting movement. By 50% you should definitely see something. No movement even with simple voltage means mechanical or wiring (or your going the wrong direction and should use negative voltages).</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":36,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T13:45:59.780Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":149,"readers_count":148,"score":34.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495759,"topic_slug":"time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so","display_username":"Jeffrey Davis","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62548,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so/495759/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558259,"name":"BBaltrusch","username":"BBaltrusch","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/c89c15/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T13:53:06.270Z","cooked":"<p>I’m another mentor on this team.  Elevator moves freely by hand and was smooth up and down when the motors ran it as straight on/off.  I don’t know much about this tuning but mechanically it seems fine.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":36,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T13:53:06.270Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":114,"readers_count":113,"score":52.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495759,"topic_slug":"time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so","display_username":"BBaltrusch","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":65795,"username":"Blengis","name":"Benji Brunner","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/blengis/{size}/223194_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":20567,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so/495759/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558297,"name":"Vincent Banks","username":"v0ncent","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/v0ncent/{size}/258352_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T14:37:01.033Z","cooked":"<p>Elevator is able to be moved with a simple command of just setting motors to x power</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":36,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T14:37:01.033Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":105,"readers_count":104,"score":21.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495759,"topic_slug":"time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so","display_username":"Vincent Banks","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":62548,"username":"Practicality","name":"Jeffrey Davis","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/practicality/{size}/208492_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":56270,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so/495759/6","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558322,"name":"Vincent Banks","username":"v0ncent","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/v0ncent/{size}/258352_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T15:11:54.542Z","cooked":"<p>we got this via our sysID tests, I will re run them</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":36,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T15:11:54.542Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":100,"readers_count":99,"score":20.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495759,"topic_slug":"time-crunch-need-help-elevator-attempts-to-move-to-setpoint-but-isnt-able-to-do-so","display_username":"Vincent Banks","primary_group_n